# CSS Property Order

Group properties by type and write them in this order within each rule:

1. **Positioning** — `position`, `top`, `right`, `bottom`, `left`, `z-index`
2. **Display & Box Model** — `display`, `flex`, `flex-direction`, `align-items`, `justify-content`, `width`, `height`, `min-width`, `max-width`, `margin`, `padding`, `overflow`
3. **Typography** — `font-family`, `font-size`, `font-weight`, `line-height`, `letter-spacing`, `text-align`, `text-decoration`, `white-space`
4. **Visual** — `background`, `background-color`, `background-image`, `border`, `border-radius`, `box-shadow`
5. **Color** — `color`, `fill`, `stroke`
6. **Misc** — `cursor`, `opacity`, `transition`, `animation`, `transform`

### Example

```css
/* ❌ BAD — mixed order */
.card {
  color: #333;
  padding: 1rem;
  position: relative;
  background: white;
  margin: 0 auto;
  font-size: 1rem;
}

/* ✅ GOOD — grouped and ordered */
.card {
  position: relative;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 1rem;
  font-size: 1rem;
  background: white;
  color: #333;
}
```

### Within a Group

Keep related properties together (e.g. `margin-top`, `margin-right`, `margin-bottom`, `margin-left` or shorthand `margin`). Prefer shorthand when all sides share the same value.
